Obtaining[edit | edit source]

Breaking[edit | edit source]

Deepslate bricks can be obtained only by mining them with any pickaxe. When mined using any other tool, they drop nothing.

Natural generation[edit | edit source]

Deepslate bricks generate naturally in ancient cities.

History[edit | edit source]

Development[edit | edit source]

February 22, 2021 JAPPA shows new texture of grimstone bricks.

Java Edition[edit | edit source]

Java Edition
1.1721w07a Added deepslate bricks, then known as grimstone bricks. At the time, they were only obtainable from the Creative inventory.
1.1721w08a Grimstone bricks have been renamed to deepslate bricks, and their texture has also been changed.
1.1721w10aAdded the crafting recipe for deepslate bricks.
1.19Deep Dark Experimental Snapshot 1Deepslate bricks now generate as part of ancient cities.

Bedrock Edition[edit | edit source]

Bedrock Edition
1.17.0beta 1.16.230.52 Added deepslate bricks.
1.20.30Preview 1.20.20.21Increased the blast resistance of both deepslate bricks from 3.6 to 6.

Issues[edit | edit source]

Issues relating to "Deepslate Bricks" are maintained on the bug tracker. Issues should be reported and viewed there.
